rough Ratnagiri Hill to reach the temple as the route goes through many hills. This trip is particularly crucial from a religious perspective since it is seen as a form of atonement for our sins. Address: Kharekhari Rd, Pushkar, Rajasthan 305022 The doors are open every day from 5:00 am to 1:30 pm. Entry is free. 6. Rangji Temple: Another well-known temple that attracts many pilgrims and visitors each year is the graceful and striking Rangji Temple. Lord Rangji, who is said to be an avatar of Lord Vishnu, is the subject of the temple. The temple's architecture influences South Indian, Rajput, and Mughal styles. Another aspect of the temple that attracts tourists is the tall "Gopuram," which is mostly found in temples in South India. Location: Rajasthan, Pushkar 305022 Opening times are from 5:00 am to 1:30 pm every day. Free entry. 7. Rose Garden: Pushkar is surprisingly well-known for its rose growing. The Rajasthan Rose Garden is the name given to Rose Garden. The farmers in this area raise a lot of different varieties of roses, which are exported all over the world. Various coloured, fragrant, and stunning red roses cover acres of farmland, enticing one to relax and spend some beautiful time. Travel to these popular Pushkar tourism destinations for an unforgettable trip with your loved ones. Activities: Take a seat, unwind, and rest while taking in the fascinating fragrance of roses. 8. Naga Pahar: The Naga Pahar hills separate Pushkar from Ajmer. According to mythology, the hills of Naga Pahar are still eroding and may soon totally disappear. The famous Sage Agastya is thought to have lived among these mountains. Nag Kund Lake is located in the mountains as well. From its height, Naga Pahar provides a magnificent view of Pushkar and is a popular destination for photographers to take pictures. It is among the top sites in Pushkar to come for a special vacation. Activities: taking pictures, short hikes, and contemplative walks Opening times: Every day Free entry. 