e without visiting the local market to buy some things. Therefore, if Pushkar is your first tourist spot, visit its namesake market. You will discover many people selling Rajasthani-inspired handicrafts, purses, souvenirs, and colourful clothing here. Rose pulp and gulkand are a couple of the specific items available here. Additionally, you may buy various leather products made from camel skin. As one of the best sites to visit in Pushkar, make sure you walk through the streets of Pushkar Bazaar. Location: Rajasthan's Pushkar Bazaar Timings: Anytime 17. In Pushkar, where can Visitors stay? In Rajasthan, Pushkar has some of the most luxurious and diverse lodging options. The top resorts in Pushkar for every price range are listed below: For luxurious facilities: Aaram Bagh and Pushkar Resort. Cheap hotels include Hotel Lake View and Hotel Lake Palace. 18. Going To Pushkar: The Pink City Express and Shatabdi Express are the top choices when travelling to Ajmer from Delhi and Jaipur. The nearest railway station is in Ajmer (11 km). Pushkar has nonstop bus service to Ajmer (30 minutes, 20 INR), Jaipur (3 hours, 220-410 INR), Udaipur (6 hours, 450 INR), and night buses to Delhi (10 hours, INR 400-850). From Jaipur, it is only 147 kilometres via road. It is one of the greatest cheap excursions in India because of how easily it can be reached from Delhi. Pushkar is not a particularly big city, so getting around is simple by walking. Here, the tour companies arrange walks and spiritual trips. Another choice is to rent a bike and explore the neighborhood. Another excellent choice for exploring the holy city is a camel safari. Next TopicTourist Places in Satara ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Ke